attributes.title: User Deep Dive - Usage Guide
attributes.visState:
{"title":"User Deep Dive - Usage Guide","type":"markdown","aggs":[],"params":{"fontSize":12,"openLinksInNewTab":false,"markdown":"# Usage Guide

Provide the target user in the search bar. The dashboard will filter results to the specified user to help streamline scoping and timeline generation.

### Event Generation
This is visual representation of volume of activity generated by the user over time.

### Login History
This is a chronological authenticated login history of the user.

### Command History
This is filtered on Sysmon Event 1 and Windows 4688. It provides the time, the system, and command executed.

### LOLBas Activity
This is filtered on Sysmon Event 1 and Windows 4688. It highlights native Windows binaries that are commonly leveraged for illegitimate purposes.

### File Creation
This is filtered on Sysmon Event 11. It provides the process that created the file and the filesystem path of the file.

### Downloads
This is filtered on Sysmon Event 15 which uses the "Mark of the Web" (an Alternate Data Stream variant) to track downloads. This is not without gaps. If a file extension doesn't support NTFS or the application ignores MotW, it will not trigger an event. But most downloads, especially those done through a browser or Outlook, will work.

### Registry Activity
Filtered on Sysmon 12 and 13. Shows registry key/value creation and modification.

### Network Connections
Filtered on Sysmon 3. This panel will show what processes are being used to establish network connections.

# Questions/Comments
Lt Goldstein - 901 CPT"}}
